<topic class="Popup" template="Default" status="Under Construction" modified="2024-03-06T10:22:33.391Z" lasteditedby="44785" version="2" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../../../helpproject.xsd">
  <title>Forces</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Forces</keyword>
    <keyword>Kinetostatic-Forces</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Kinetostatic Forces</text> are those reaction forces on <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Parts </text>at <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Joints, 2D-</text>Cams and Gears, that result from the motions that are designed and imposed on them. </para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">Also, the <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Torque</text> or <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Force</text> that a motor must provide to move each kinematic-chain with the motions that you design for them - sometimes called the <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Application-Load</text>, particularly when sizing a motor.</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">We also use the terms: </para>
          <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Drive Torque</text>, which is the <text styleclass="VariableName-small">turning moment</text> a Rotary Motor, or Servomotor, must provide to the kinematic-chain.</li>
            <li styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Drive</text> (or <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Motive</text>) <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Force</text> as the <text styleclass="VariableName-small">linear force</text> a <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Linear Motor</text> must provide to the kinematic-chain.</li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
</topic>
